OL,3,CHow will social media ban for under-
OL,4,C16s work and which apps are affected?
OL,6,FHowever, a March report by Australia's
OL,7,Fnational independent regulator for
OL,8,Fonline safety found that 70% of
OL,9,Fchildren with social media accounts
OL,10,Fbefore the ban still had access to
OL,11,Fthem.
OL,13,FAround 67% of parents said their
OL,14,Fchildren still had accounts because
OL,15,Fthey hadn't been asked to verify their
OL,16,Fage, and platform-led deactivation was
OL,17,Fgiven as the most common reason for
OL,18,Fthose without access, the eSafety
OL,19,FCommissioner found.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
